FSL100H1-F-20209.courseDescription: An intensive basic course in spoken and written French for students who have no knowledge of French: comprehension, speaking, reading, and writing.
FSL100H1-F-20209.webTimetableInstructions: This is a 3-hour course (2-hr lecture, 1-hr tutorial). Students will be assigned a tutorial by the instructor at the beginning of classes. Students with NO previous knowledge of French will enroll in this course and are NOT required to do the online placement test.
FSL100H1-F-20209.deliveryInstructions:
For dual delivery, sign up for: LEC5101 and TUT5101 or LEC5101 & TUT5102 (lecture and tutorials will be in-person if conditions permit, plus online synchronous). 

For online synchronous, sign up for: LEC0101 and LEC0201, along with TUT0101 & TUT0201. 

LEC0301 sign up for TUT0301.

FSL100H1-S-20209.courseDescription: An intensive basic course in spoken and written French for students who have no knowledge of French: comprehension, speaking, reading, and writing.
FSL100H1-S-20209.webTimetableInstructions: This is a 3-hour course (2-hr lecture, 1-hr tutorial). Students will be assigned a tutorial by the instructor at the beginning of classes. Students with NO previous knowledge of French will enroll in this course and are NOT required to do the online placement test.

FSL102H1-S-20209.courseDescription: An intensive basic course in spoken and written French for students who have studied some French, but who have not yet attained the entry level for FSL121Y1.
FSL102H1-S-20209.prerequisite: FSL100H1 or, upon first FRE/FSL enrolment, equivalent as determined by the French Placement Test.
FSL102H1-S-20209.webTimetableInstructions: This is a 3-hour course (2-hr lecture, 1-hr tutorial). Students will be assigned a tutorial by the instructor at the beginning of classes. The placement test www.lang.utoronto.ca/placement/french is mandatory for students with a minimum knowledge of French.

FSL121Y1-Y-20209.courseDescription: Intended for students having some knowledge of French but wishing to increase their proficiency to that of normal University entrance. Offers training in written and spoken French; reinforcement of reading comprehension and aural abilities; and an introduction to French-Canadian and Québécois cultures.
FSL121Y1-Y-20209.prerequisite: FSL102H1, or, upon first FRE/FSL enrolment, equivalent as determined by the French Placement Test.
FSL121Y1-Y-20209.webTimetableInstructions: This is a 4-hour course (2-hr lecture, 2-hr tutorial). Students must enroll in both the lecture and the tutorial for a total of four hours per week. Students should check for any schedule conflict before enrolling in a tutorial. Changing or switching of lecture meeting or tutorial at mid-session is not permitted at the Department of French. Students who are not enrolled in the tutorial of their choice by the enrolment deadline will be placed by the Department of French in another section according to availability. The placement test www.lang.utoronto.ca/placement/french is mandatory for students who do not have the prerequisites.
FSL121Y1-Y-20209.deliveryInstructions:
LEC0101 Online synchronous: 2hr Lecture online synchronous + 2 hr TUT Online synchronous (TUT 0101 or TUT 0201)

LEC5101 Dual Delivery (lecture will be in-person if conditions permit, plus online synchronous, TUT will be online synchronous): 2 hrs in class lecture + 2 hrs TUT online synchronous (TUT 0301 or TUT 5101)

FSL221Y1-Y-20209.courseDescription: Intended for those who have some knowledge of French, this course is the first in a proficiency-sequenced series that provides students with the opportunity to become proficient, focused, autonomous French language learners. Adopting a principally actional approach to second language learning targeting Level A2 objectives of the Common European Framework of Reference for Languages (CEFR), the course’s main objective is to provide a communicative learning environment through activities based in real-world, everyday contexts.
FSL221Y1-Y-20209.prerequisite: FSL121Y1 or, upon first FRE/FSL enrolment, equivalent as determined by the French Placement Test.
FSL221Y1-Y-20209.webTimetableInstructions: This is a 3-hr course (2-hr lecture, 1-hr tutorial).  Students must enroll in both the lecture and tutorial for a total of 3 hours per week. Students should check for any schedule conflict before enrolling in a tutorial. Changing or switching of lecture meeting or tutorial at mid-session is not permitted at the Department of French. Students who are not enrolled in the tutorial of their choice by the enrolment deadline will be placed by the Department of French in another section according to availability. The placement test www.lang.utoronto.ca/placement/french is mandatory for students who do not have the prerequisites.
FSL221Y1-Y-20209.deliveryInstructions:
LEC 0101: 1h LEC Online Synchronous (FR 10h-11h) + 1 h LEC  Online Asynchronous +  1hr TUT online synchronous (TUT 0101 or TUT 0102)

LEC 0201: 1h LEC Online Synchronous (TU 10h-11h) + 1 h LEC Online Asynchronous + 1 hr TUT online synchronous (TUT 0201 or TUT 0202) 

LEC 5101: 1 h LEC Online Synchronous (MO 18-19h) + 1 h LEC Online Asynchronous + 1 hr TUT online synchronous (TUT 5101 or TUT 5102)

For online synchronous only, sign up for: LEC0301 plus TUT 0301 or TUT 0302, LEC0401 + TUT 0401 or TUT 0402.

FSL312H1-S-20209.courseTitle: Writing French: the Language of the Media
FSL312H1-S-20209.courseDescription: Using current online French media, broaden your understanding of the French language; deepen your grammatical knowledge; expand your vocabulary (including idioms); review key aspects of French syntax; and fine-tune your reading skills in French. Weekly reading and writing workshops are an integral part of this course.
FSL312H1-S-20209.prerequisite: FSL221Y1 (63%) or, upon first FRE/FSL enrolment equivalent as determined by the French Placement Test.
FSL312H1-S-20209.webTimetableInstructions: The placement test www.lang.utoronto.ca/placement/french is mandatory for students who do not have the prerequisites.

FSL313H1-F-20209.courseDescription:
This course is designed to enhance students’ existing knowledge of French by giving them a theoretical as well as a practical foundation in the use of French language in the workplace. Special emphasis will be placed on the appropriate vocabulary used within the context of communication in the Francophone workplace. Students will learn how to communicate in a variety of professional contexts as well as how to distinguish between the formal and informal styles of French suitable for diverse situations in the workplace. This course also aims to help students acquire intercultural skills needed in the Francophone workplace.

The redesigned course will provide a hybrid alternative that delivers the same high quality content and high degree of interaction present in traditional in-class course delivery. The new format will consist of weekly one-hour online sessions and two-hour traditional in-class sessions. In this format, further preparation work and homework will continue to be carried on as in the traditional course, i.e. outside of the 3-hour class time.
FSL313H1-F-20209.prerequisite: FSL221Y1 (63%) or, upon first FRE/FSL, enrolment equivalent as determined by the French Placement Test
FSL313H1-F-20209.webTimetableInstructions: The placement test www.lang.utoronto.ca/placement/french is mandatory for students who do not have the prerequisites.
FSL313H1-F-20209.deliveryInstructions: 2 hours LEC Online Synchronous (WE 12h-14h) + 1 hour LEC Online Asynchronous

FSL313H1-S-20209.deliveryInstructions: 2-hr LEC ONL SYNC WE 13:00-15:00; 1-hr LEC ONL ASYNC

FSL315H1-S-20209.courseTitle: French Oral Communication for Professional and Academic Contexts
FSL315H1-S-20209.courseDescription: This course is designed for students who wish to develop their oral communication skills in French in preparation for bilingual employment, community service, and academic activities in Canada and abroad. Emphasis is placed on the development of skills for accurate oral language use in professional and academic contexts: researched oral presentations, debates, interviews, and student-led discussions. Students will learn how to adapt their speaking style and register to different audiences and situations, use appropriate vocabulary, and self-correct.
FSL315H1-S-20209.prerequisite: FSL221Y1 (63%) or, upon first FRE/FSL, enrolment equivalent as determined by the French Placement Test
FSL315H1-S-20209.exclusion: FSL321Y1 and higher. Not open to fluent and native speakers of French.
FSL315H1-S-20209.webTimetableInstructions: The placement test www.lang.utoronto.ca/placement/french is mandatory for students who do not have the prerequisites.

FSL321Y1-Y-20209.courseDescription: The course is intended for students who have already mastered the basic competences in French language proficiency. The textbook used in this course will follow the B1 level of the Common European Framework of Reference for Languages (CEFR) in its active approach which puts emphasis on the student being at the centre of the learning process. Students will learn the following intermediate-level language skills: writing, speaking as well as understanding written and spoken French.
FSL321Y1-Y-20209.prerequisite: FSL221Y1 (63%) or, upon first FRE/FSL enrolment, equivalent as determined by the French Placement Test
FSL321Y1-Y-20209.exclusion: FSL375Y1 and higher. May not be taken concurrently with any FSL31*H1 series courses.
FSL321Y1-Y-20209.webTimetableInstructions: This is a 3-hour course (2-hr lecture, 1-hr tutorial). Students will be assigned a tutorial by the instructor at the beginning of classes. Changing or switching of lecture meeting or tutorial at mid-session is not permitted at the Department of French. The placement test www.lang.utoronto.ca/placement/french is mandatory for students who do not have the prerequisites.
FSL321Y1-Y-20209.deliveryInstructions:
LEC 0101: 1 hour LEC Online Sync (MO 10h-11h) + 1 hour LEC Online Asynchronous

LEC 0201: 1 hour LEC Online Sync (TU 10h-11h) + 1 hour LEC Online Asynchronous

LEC 5101: 1 hour LEC Online Sync (TU 17-18) + 1 hour LEC Online Asynchronous

Students must also enroll for 1hr TUT Online Synchronous

FSL375Y1-Y-20209.courseDescription: This full-year course, which works as an introduction to translation, is designed to improve students’ mastery of French through English to French and French to English translations. Emphasis is on the practice of translation of a variety of texts and documents, and on the introduction to the practice of oral interpretation from one language to the other.
FSL375Y1-Y-20209.prerequisite: 1.0 FCE in FSL at the 300-level, or any 1.0 FCE in FRE at the 200-level.
FSL375Y1-Y-20209.webTimetableInstructions: The placement test www.lang.utoronto.ca/placement/french is mandatory for students who do not have the prerequisites.
FSL375Y1-Y-20209.deliveryInstructions: Dual delivery: (lecture  MO 12:00-15:00) will be in-person if conditions permit, plus online synchronous).

FSL421Y1-Y-20209.courseDescription: An advanced course in French including the reading and discussion of texts focussing on the francophone presence and influence in the international context. Emphasis is placed on mastery of complex linguistic skills via use of a variety of reference tools and self-correction.
FSL421Y1-Y-20209.prerequisite: FSL321Y1 or, upon first FRE/FSL enrolment, equivalent as determined by the French Placement Test.
FSL421Y1-Y-20209.webTimetableInstructions: The placement test www.lang.utoronto.ca/placement/french is mandatory for students who do not have the prerequisites. Changing or switching of lecture meeting or tutorial at mid-session is not permitted at the Department of French.
FSL421Y1-Y-20209.deliveryInstructions:
LEC 0101: 2 hrs LEC Online Asynchronous + 1h TUT ONL Synchronous (TU 14h-15h)

LEC 0201: 2 hrs LEC Online Asynchronous + 1h TUT ONL Synchronous (TH 14h-15h)

FSL442H1-F-20209.courseDescription: Designed for students who wish to consolidate and perfect their writing abilities. Skills developped include the mastery of register-based differences; use of rhetorical and stylistic techniques; systematic self-correction; and the advanced use of reference tools including on-line dictionaries.
FSL442H1-F-20209.prerequisite: FSL421Y1 or, upon first FRE/FSL enrolment, equivalent as determined by the French Placement Test
FSL442H1-F-20209.webTimetableInstructions: The placement test www.lang.utoronto.ca/placement/french is mandatory for students who do not have the prerequisites.

FSL473H1-S-20209.courseDescription: Putting students in diverse speaking and listening situations and contexts, this course is designed for those who wish to consolidate and perfect their speaking and listening abilities and take them to the next level. Focusing on a contextual approach of both oral and aural French and various francophone cultures, this course will focus on various aspects and difficulties that come with speaking and understanding French in real-life situations.
FSL473H1-S-20209.exclusion: Not open to fluent or native speakers of French.
FSL473H1-S-20209.webTimetableInstructions: The placement test www.lang.utoronto.ca/placement/french is mandatory for students who do not have the prerequisites.
